                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="destpet/components/content/richtext"
                            text="&lt;p>We welcome dogs of all breeds, sizes, and ages as long as they are in good overall health and free from communicable diseases and internal and external parasites. Your dog must also be up to date on their Rabies, DAPP (Distemper, Adenovirus, Parainfluenza, and Parvovirus), Bordetella, and Bivalent Canine Influenza vaccines, we perform all vaccination and spay/neuter service. If your pup is over six months of age and you’d like them to play with other dogs, they must also be spayed or neutered.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>We ask that you provide your dog’s food in meal-sized bags. We do offer a number of our own safe and yummy treats as well! Kindly contact us to inquire about ingredients and pricing. You are also required to provide any medication your pet needs. For the health and safety of your pet, please include dosage instructions along with their prescriptions.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Our facility has various accommodations to meet your pet’s needs. Bringing your pet to us is like taking them on their own fun-filled vacation!&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
